Closed date : 2015-12-03 12:16:34.007 Case Noted Thank you for your comments regarding the Hempfest  also known by its   organizers as The Boston Freedom Rally.  �  The Boston Parks and Recreation Department has legally challenged on multiple   occasions dating back to the 1990s.� The courts have allowed the event to continue   despite our concerns over illicit drug use  damage to park property  and amplified   music.� We must respect these court decisions and the First Amendment rights of   the participants.� �For those who have suggested that the event be moved to another   park location  please note that the organizers specifically request that the event be   held on Boston Common and we have no say in that part of their application.  �  We will continue to work with the City of Boston Law Department to discuss our   options moving forward.� Your support and input is invaluable to this process.� We   are currently collecting written comments that we will present as discussions of   this matter move forward.  �  Please understand that we are constrained by past legal decisions interpreting this   as an event protected by free speech but we will continue to work to mitigate   impacts on the Common and the community as best we can.  �  Chris Cook  Commissioner
SUBJECT: Parks & Recreation Department
